                    <span>My husband and I found this very useful when our child was first diagnosed, I was always referring to the list of terms and the pictures.<p>My only regret is that of another review in that the  statistical information is out of date.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Congenital Heart Defects</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>4</span>
                      /
                      <span>5</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>1999-12-18</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>As parents of two children with congenital heart defects, we found this book to be a wonderful resource.  It is a must buy for parents who find themselves faced with the prospect of raising a child with a heart  condition.  This book does a wonderful job of describing the types of heart  defects in terms the average person can understand.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Very good, but the information seems outdated.</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
